			    STPJS 191</div>
  <div class="topic">ITEMS OF INSTRUCTION</div>
  <div class="topic">Baptism for the Dead</div>
  <p class="std">President Joseph Smith, by request of the Twelve Apostles, gave instructions on the doctrine
  of baptism for the dead,<span class="footRef">1</span> which were listened to with intense interest by the large assembly. He
  presented baptism for the dead as the only way that men can appear as saviors on Mount Zion.<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <p class="std">The proclamation of the first principles of the Gospel<span class="footRef">3</span> was a means of salvation<span class="footRef">4</span> to men
  individually; and it was the truth, not men, that saved them;<span class="footRef">5</span> but men, by actively engaging<span class="footRef">6</span> in rites
  of salvation substitutionally<span class="footRef">7</span> became instrumental in bringing multitudes of their kindred into the
  kingdom of God.<span class="footRef">8</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Angels and Ministering Spirits</div>
  <p class="std">He explained the difference between an angel<span class="footRef">9</span> and a ministering spirit;<span class="footRef">10</span> the one a resurrected
  or translated body, with its spirit ministering to embodied spirits&mdash;the other a disembodied spirit,
  visiting and ministering to disembodied spirits. Jesus Christ became a ministering spirit (while His
  body was lying in the sepulchre) to the spirits in prison,<span class="footRef">11</span> to fulfill an important part of His mission,
  without which He could not have perfected His work,<span class="footRef">12</span> or entered into His rest.<span class="footRef">13</span> After His
  resurrection He appeared<span class="footRef">14</span> as an angel to His disciples.<span class="footRef">15</span></p>
  <p class="std">Translated bodies<span class="footRef">16</span> cannot enter into rest until they have undergone a change equivalent to
  death.<span class="footRef">17</span> Translated bodies are designed for future missions.</p>
  <p class="std">The angel that appeared to John<span class="footRef">18</span> on the Isle of Patmos was a translated or resurrected body
  [i.e., personage]. Jesus Christ went in body after His resurrection, to minister to resurrected bodies.
  There has been a chain of authority and power from Adam down to the present time.</p>
  <p class="std">The best way to obtain truth and wisdom<span class="footRef">19</span> is not to ask it from books,<span class="footRef">20</span> but to go to God in
  prayer,<span class="footRef">21</span> and obtain divine teaching. It is no more incredible that God should <i>save</i> the dead,<span class="footRef">22</span> than
  that he should <i>raise</i> the dead.<span class="footRef">23</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Pardoning Mercy an Eternal Principle</div>
  <p class="std">There is never a time when the spirit is too old<span class="footRef">24</span> to approach God.<span class="footRef">25</span> All are within the reach of
  pardoning mercy,<span class="footRef">26</span> who have not committed the unpardonable sin,<span class="footRef">27</span> which hath no forgiveness,<span class="footRef">28</span></p>
